 THE ██████ BURRITO
"...more fun than a fortune cookie, and at least as accurate."

=0F"Are those folks smoking crack?=0F" ██ asked in an outrage.  My friend, =
Ol=0F'
████ in ███████, has trouble understanding the workings of our power
business here in ██████████.  In fact, so do ████Yesterday=0F's Joint
█████████████████████████████████████████████████████████ did nothing to
improve either ████=0F's or my understanding of the national embarrassment
██████████ is perpetrating with electricity deregulation.

=0F"The next thing you know, they will be taking property, and forcing
utilities to build power plants and transmission,=0F" ██ mused between sips
of █████ longneck beer and chomps of jalapeno peppers.  =0F"Come to think
of it, ████, they did say something about that. Yeah,=0F" I recalled,
=0F"Senator Peace was expounding on ███ favorite idea which is forcing the
███ or the utilities to build peakers, and not let the market build
them.  I can=0F't remember if that was before or after ██ suggested to ███
Chairman ████ that ███████ and the ██ should be folded into █████
agencies under the direction of ██████████████████████ Board.=0F"

I know what you are thinking right now.  The next thing you know
██████████ will have regulated retail rates.  That recipe should be out
of ███████=0F's oven ██████████████████.

=0F"Well, the power marketers are jigging the system, bidding up to the
███=0F's bid cap.   There is no way you can tell me that a generator
planned to make $750/MWH in its pro forma,=0F" ████ added. =0F"So you agree
with ████ (Hair) Peace!  You don=0F't believe in markets,=0F" I retorted. =
=0F"Oh,
I believe in them, but I remember when I was short on a 300 MW trade,
and without any notice or advanced warning, the price in ███████████
market went against me,=0F" ████ recalled.  =0F"I called everyone who I tra=
ded
with, and they had nothing.  I finally called XXXXX, and I asked what
will it cost for 50 MW?=0F"

=0F"Why didn=0F't you ask for 300?=0F" I wondered.  =0F"I didn=0F't want to=
 show ███ my
position.  You get hosed when you show the buyer your position.  Ask for
50, first,=0F" ████ chided.

=0F"What happened?=0F" =0F"Oh, they offered to sell for $150/MWH.  I said I=
=0F'd
take it, and then said I needed another fifty.  ██ asked $300.  I took
that, and ██ priced the next 50 MW at $600,=0F" lamented ████.  =0F"██ just
wanted to see how far ██ could push me. ███████'s what I mean when I say
the traders are jigging it.=0F"

=0F"But ████, you old communist, your forgetting the trading function is
what mitigates the risk. The traders are the in between people who guess
at the price.  Sometimes they guess right, and sometimes they guess
wrong.  But the damage, or the reward, is on their book, not passed on
to the ultimate consumer. It has nothing to do with the marginal cost of
a generating plant.=0F"

And there you have it.  Put in a price cap, and the traders have a
target for which to shoot.  I can=0F't prove the following, yet, but I=0F'l=
l
wager with any of you that as the price cap level dips down, the average
trading price climbs even as the so-called =0F"dysfunctional=0F" price spik=
es
are eliminated.  Consumers get hosed, and the fundamental economic
principle is upheld, which is, one can never be made better off with the
imposition of an additional constraint.

I feel better already.  Here is what is on our short agenda █████████.

