 @@@ Reflections on a Day of ██████ Hearings

If you want to imagine a scary sight, imagine, then, twelve ██████████
legislators gathering together in one hearing room to rectify the wrongs
of electric restructuring.  Also imagine, as if you are in the Twilight
Zone, witnesses that are slow on their feet, and reckless in their
facts.  Then you get a glimpse of what █████████=0F's Joint ██████/Assembly
hearing was like.

It started over two hours late.  The ██████ was busy congratulating one
of their own who is term-limited out next session, and they wanted to
heap on the glory.  That said, the show began with ███ ██████████er Bill
█████.  Mr. █████ has one story, and regardless how well ██ tells it,
and ██ does, it is always the same story.  It is the heat storm story.
One can imagine in the heat storm story a lead character who is a
single-mom, call ███ Lady-Bird █████, who travels across an angry land
with ███ precocious pre-teen child, ████████████████.  They are
searching for electric power plants in the dessert, which, by the grace
of God have been shipped to other countries which have more liberal
returns on investment.

Being the first speaker, Mr. █████ took at least half the heat (storm)
of ███████.  The rage of the Energy ██████ was palpable.  █████████, ███
Diegans shed 350 MW of load █████████ to save the entire system, and did
not receive one penny of compensation (I=0F'm not making that up ... ██
said it).  ██ is sick of hearing about demand management as being a
solution for the problem over ███████████████████, and ██ is about done
listening.  People in █████████ are depressed by the sudden price
hikes.  █████!

█████ did mention that ██████████████ reserve margin has sunk to 7%, but
in neighboring ███████, the reserve margin is -1% or -2%!!  Mr. █████
correctly pointed out that electric power is not solely a ██████████
problem, it is a regional problem.  One member of █████████████ asked
what the legislature could do to speed up the power plant siting and
construction process?

█████ referred to Governor ██████████████ ███████████████ issued █████████
to which ███████ plans to respond soon, date uncertain, that lays out a
███████ permitting time line.  The ██████████ are enough if the
applicant has the land secured, zoning okayed, transmission access, and
air offsets.  Hmmmmmm.  That alone might take ██████████ before you get
to ███████.

The next panel included Mr. ████ of ███████, and Ms. █████.  I went too
hard on ███ █████████, calling ███ Let=0F's Do █████.  That was a 0.8 ███.
Sorry.  I promise to be nicer starting now.  The Energy ██████
instructed Ms. █████ to use ███ authority to order SDG&E to divert the
pass through of funds from the customers to the ██ until the dysfunction
of the market is cured.  Put it in an escrow account.  Ms █████ promised
to review this option at ███ █████████████ Meeting where ███ will enact
SDG&E rate caps (told you).

The star of ███████, I thought, was ████ General Counsel ██████████.
Mr. █████ comes to ██████████.  Isn=0F't that a switch?  Mr. █████ came in
place of Mr. ███████, thank the Lord.  Mr. █████ put into ████-eese what
these 12 legislators could not get through their heads any other way.
The 12 angry legislators were looking for a way for ████ to declare the
wholesale market as non-competitive, and then ask the generators to give
back the money they over collected.  When can we do that?  Mr. █████
answered as only a ████ attorney can answer.  There is a process.  It
takes time.  You must have evidence.  ████ uses a three-part criteria
for assessing whether or not market based rates are allowable.  █████'s
based on market concentration and dominance, not the existence of high
prices.  You would have to sue ████ in federal court, and the best you
could hope for is for ████ to reconsider its decision upon remand from
███████████████████████.

Slowly, the wind came out of the sails of the gang of 12.  They were
stumped.  ████ (Hair?) Peace screamed, couldn=0F't you, Mr. █████ of ████,
█████ use your authority to declare the markets non-competitive, that
generators who had market based rates have exercised market power, and
retro-actively implement a $250 rate cap across the Western region?
Like a wheezing accordion, Mr. █████ played back and forth the familiar
strains of music, like a solo street musician on the corner.  Back and
forth: the process, the process, the process.  There have been times in
the past I hated the process at ████.  Today, I have a renewed respect
for what process affords me and you ... Freedom from the tyranny of a
mob.

For the remainder of the hearing, they focused on remedies that could be
undertaken by ███████.

